The paper focuses on crowdsourcing and machine learning, which are both interdisciplinary topics. However, the emphasis on non-expert workers proposing supervised learning problems and providing data for predictive models suggests a strong connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses feature engineering and predictive modeling, which are core topics in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper touches on topics such as politics, health behavior, and demographics, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
